{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: collectors -> aggregation/orchestration -> summary input payload. A unit test of a single mapper can miss wiring/omission bugs, but real OS/network is not required if source clients are in-process fakes. Rejected System because behavior text only requires verifying combined payload content, not real HTTP/network behavior. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because this behavior does not judge model output, only pre-summary input assembly.","test_description":"Run the report pipeline with three fake source adapters returning distinct sentinel fields/values and assert the exact payload sent into the summary-generation interface contains all three source sections and expected key fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is resilience logic across modules (source adapter failure handling + report composition). Real infra outage is not strictly needed to catch the core failure; an adapter fake raising timeout/connection exceptions can reproduce it. Rejected System because behavior text focuses fallback behavior in report output, not true network/OS semantics. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness is deterministic fallback handling, not model judgment.","test_description":"Configure one source adapter to fail (e.g., exception), two others to return data, execute report generation, and assert process completes, includes `data unavailable` in the failed section, and still contains other sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on summary content quality (faithfulness to key values), which is model-output dependent if summary generation is AI/ML based. Stubbed outputs would hide hallucination/omission distortions. Rejected Workflow because behavior describes one model judgment step (summary faithfulness), not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Use representative real report inputs with known key values, call the real summary-generation model, and evaluate whether produced narrative preserves/reflects those key values (with rubric or evaluator checks) across repeated runs to detect variability-driven failures.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery/inbox behavior (SMTP/API transport, authentication, routing, inbox receipt). In-process mocks can pass while real delivery fails. Rejected Agentic because this behavior asserts end-to-end delivery success, not summary quality/decision correctness; summary content can be deterministic fixture for this test objective. Rejected Workflow because no requirement here for multiple agentic decisions.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled report job end-to-end against reachable test instances/services and a real test mailbox, then assert email is received by configured recipient, subject/body/attachments are present, and report content corresponds to that run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior spans real failure mode plus persistence/retry across runs: unreachable delivery service, durable local file fallback, and later scheduled retry. Mock-only tests can miss filesystem path/permission/atomic-write and real reconnect/retry timing issues. Rejected Workflow because retry logic is deterministic orchestration, not chained model decisions.","test_description":"Run job with email endpoint intentionally unreachable, assert report is persisted to actual local fallback path; run next scheduled execution with email restored, assert persisted report is retried and successfully delivered, and fallback artifact state is updated/cleared as designed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
